{"questionId":"00907d99-e579-47a8-ac65-658aadef4aa7_11","correctAnswer":"4","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Factor the second equation","content":"Rewrite: $\\dfrac{cx}{4y}=\\dfrac{c}{4}\\cdot\\dfrac{x}{y}=76$."},{"title":"Combine and compute","content":"Substitute $\\dfrac{x}{y}=76$: $\\dfrac{c}{4}\\cdot 76=76$, so $\\dfrac{c}{4}=1$ and $c=4$.<br/><br/>The answer is <strong>4</strong>."}]}